#: casca/help_content.py:81
msgid "Check <strong>Customize icon and shortcut</strong> to choose manually."
msgstr "Zaznacz <strong>Dostosuj ikonę i skrót</strong>, aby wybrać ręcznie."

#: casca/help_content.py:82 casca/window.py:349
msgid "Search online"
msgstr "Szukaj online"

#: casca/help_content.py:84
msgid ""
"Checks several sources — Google, DuckDuckGo, apple-touch-icon, PWA manifest "
"— and shows the results in a grid."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:87 casca/window.py:351
msgid "From computer"
msgstr "Z komputera"

#: casca/help_content.py:88
msgid "Picks a PNG, JPG or SVG file already saved on your computer."
msgstr "Wybiera plik PNG, JPG lub SVG już zapisany na komputerze."

#: casca/help_content.py:89 casca/window.py:353
msgid "From gallery"
msgstr "Z galerii"

#: casca/help_content.py:90
msgid "Over 160 brand icons already included, no internet needed."
msgstr "Ponad 160 ikon marek już dołączonych, internet niepotrzebny."

#: casca/help_content.py:92
msgid ""
"Without checking anything, Casca fetches an icon automatically on save — or "
"uses the icon that's already set, if the app came from a preset."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:95
msgid "Desktop Shortcut"
msgstr "Skrót na pulpicie"

#: casca/help_content.py:97
msgid ""
"Every app already shows up in the GNOME applications menu. To also get an "
"icon on the Desktop, check <strong>Customize icon and shortcut</strong> and "
"turn on <strong>Also create on the Desktop</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:101
msgid "Custom browser"
msgstr "Własna przeglądarka"

#: casca/help_content.py:103
msgid ""
"By default, every app opens in <strong>Casca's own window</strong>: lighter, "
"top bar automatically colored to match the icon, isolated session per app."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:107
msgid ""
"<strong>Heads up:</strong> sites with Google login (Gmail, Drive, Calendar, "
"Meet…) tend to refuse login in the built-in window — a Google restriction "
"against unrecognized browsers, with no workaround. Check <strong>Use a "
"custom browser</strong> and pick Chrome, Helium, GNOME Web or another "
"installed browser."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:113
msgid ""
"With a Chromium-based browser (Chrome, Chromium, Brave, Edge, Vivaldi, "
"Helium…) and more than one account configured in it, <strong>Browser "
"account</strong> also shows up — choose which already-logged-in account "
"opens the app, instead of a new profile with no login."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:120
msgid ""
"Check <strong>Open in mobile mode</strong> and pick a device — Google Pixel, "
"iPhone, Galaxy, iPad. The app identifies itself to the site as that device, "
"unlocking the mobile layout (usually simpler and faster)."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:124
msgid "Window resolution"
msgstr "Rozdzielczość okna"

#: casca/help_content.py:126
msgid ""
"Check <strong>Customize window resolution</strong> — three ways to set the "
"size, works with or without mobile mode enabled."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:130
msgid ""
"<strong>By device</strong> — uses the screen size of the device chosen in "
"mobile mode."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:132
msgid "<strong>Default size</strong> — common resolutions (laptop, Full HD…)."
msgstr "<strong>Domyślny rozmiar</strong> — popularne rozdzielczości (laptop, Full HD…)."

#: casca/help_content.py:133
msgid "<strong>Custom</strong> — you type in width and height in pixels."
msgstr "<strong>Niestandardowa</strong> — wpisujesz szerokość i wysokość w pikselach."

#: casca/help_content.py:134
msgid "Edit and delete"
msgstr "Edytuj i usuń"

#: casca/help_content.py:136
msgid ""
"On the home screen, every app has a pencil to <strong>edit</strong> (changes "
"any setting, including ones that were disabled at creation) and a trash icon "
"to <strong>delete</strong> (removes the shortcut from the menu, the Desktop, "
"and the saved icon)."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:141
msgid "Casca — built to turn websites into GNOME apps."
msgstr "Casca — stworzona, by zamieniać strony w aplikacje GNOME."

